<h1 align="center"><b><font size="5" color="#0000FF">General Help</font></b></h1>
<table class="paragrpahnospace" id="table3" cellSpacing="2" cellPadding="4" width="750" border="0">
	<tr>
		<td bgColor="#d2e4ee" height="27"><b><font size="4">System Requirements</font></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td bgColor="#ffffff" height="27">
    <p><u><b>Web Browser</b></u></p>
    <p>Internet Explorer version 6.0 SP1 or higher is required to use the site.  However, Internet Explorer 8 is not supported yet.  So Internet Explorer 6 or 7 are the only web browsers supported.</p>
    <p>No web browser software other than Internet Explorer is supported.  For example, the list of unsupported web browsers includes but is not limited to: Mozilla Firefox, Apple Safari, Google Chrome, Opera.</p>
    <p>Recommended screen resolution is 1024 x 768 or higher.</p>
    <font SIZE="3"><u><b><p ALIGN="LEFT">Finding the Internet Explorer Version
		</p>
		</b></u></font><font FACE="LONEFC+Arial,Arial" SIZE="2">
		<p ALIGN="LEFT">To check which version of Internet 
		Explorer your computer is using, open any Internet web page. </p>
		</font>
		<dir>
			<dir>
				<font FACE="LONEFC+Arial,Arial" SIZE="2">
				<p ALIGN="LEFT">• Click "Help" on the tool bar at the top of the 
				window menu, </p>
				</font><font FACE="LONEFC+Arial,Arial" SIZE="3">
				<p ALIGN="LEFT"></p>
				</font><font FACE="LONEFC+Arial,Arial" SIZE="2">
				<p ALIGN="LEFT">• Click "About Internet Explorer" on the drop down 
				menu that appears. </p>
				</font><font FACE="LONEFC+Arial,Arial" SIZE="3">
				<p ALIGN="LEFT"></p>
				</font><font FACE="LONEFC+Arial,Arial" SIZE="2">
				<p ALIGN="LEFT">• A window will open, and the first line will 
				tell you which version you are currently running on your 
				computer; and the fourth line down will provide you with the 
				latest Update versions added to your computer. </font></p>
			</dir>
		</dir>
	<tr>
		<td bgColor="#ffffff" height="27">
    <p><u><b>Operating System</b></u></p>
    <p>Windows 2000 or later is required to use this site.  For best results, use Windows XP.</p>
    <p>For best results, always make sure your operating system is up to date by using "Windows Update".</p>
    <p>You can access "Windows Update" by opening your Internet Explorer web browser, clicking on the "Tools" menu, and selecting the "Windows Update" option and following the instructions on the website you are taken to.  However, please remember to not update to Internet Explorer 8, as it is not yet supported for using this site.
    </p>
    </td>
	</tr>
    <tr>
    <td bgColor="#ffffff">
		<font SIZE="2">
    <p><b>Work Computer Troubleshooting Instructions</b></p>
		<p ALIGN="LEFT"><font face="LONEFC+Arial,Arial">If you are currently 
		using an older version of Internet Explorer prior to 6 on your <b>work</b> computer, please contact the St. Luke's Help Desk at 381-4357 so they can upgrade your software.</font></p>
    <p><b>Home Computer Troubleshooting Instructions</b></p>
		<p><font face="LONEFC+Arial,Arial">If you are attempting to access this 
		from your <b>home</b> computer and it does not meet the above criteria, the easiest way to upgrade your version of
    Internet Explorer is by running "Windows Update" which will get the latest web browser from the Microsoft Website.  However, Internet Explorer 8 is not supported yet, only Internet Explorer 6 and 7 are supported.
    </p>
    <p>You can access "Windows Update" by opening your Internet Explorer web browser, clicking on the "Tools" menu, and selecting the "Windows Update" option and following the instructions on the website you are taken to.        
    </font></font>

    </td>
	</tr>


